    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1922: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-19T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 19, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>279. Your 327, October 17. Department concurs in your recommendation regarding
                    assurance to be given Iranian Government if Sheridan determines wheat supply
                    will be insufficient to last until <pb facs="0170" n="158" xml:id="pg_158"/>
                    next harvest. However, you should give no guarantee to Iranians pending further
                    instructions. We are sending summary of your telegram to London and instructing
                    London Embassy to endeavor to obtain British agreement to joint assurance.
                        Winant<note n="51" xml:id="d175fn51">Frederick Winant, United States
                        civilian representative on Middle East Supply Center.</note> at Cairo is
                    also being informed and authorized in his discretion to take question up with
                    British Middle East authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
